### AgentPayWatch API — HTTP request file
### Base URL: HTTP port is fixed in launchSettings.json — works with Aspire and direct dotnet run
@host = https://localhost:53566
@userId = user-abc123
@watchId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Root
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### GET / — health check / root label
GET {{host}} HTTP/1.1

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// POST /api/watches — Create a new watch request
// Response 201: WatchResponse { id, userId, productName, maxPrice, currency,
//   preferredSellers, approvalMode, autoApproveThreshold, notificationChannel,
//   status, createdAt, updatedAt }
// Response 400: string (validation error)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create watch — minimal (required fields only)
POST {{host}}/api/watches?userId={{userId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productName": "Sony WH-1000XM5",
  "maxPrice": 279.99
}

###

### Create watch — full payload (all optional fields)
POST {{host}}/api/watches?userId={{userId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productName": "MacBook Pro 14\"",
  "maxPrice": 1799.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "preferredSellers": ["Apple", "BestBuy", "Amazon"]
}

###

### Create watch — invalid: missing productName → 400
POST {{host}}/api/watches?userId={{userId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productName": "",
  "maxPrice": 299.99
}

###

### Create watch — invalid: maxPrice = 0 → 400
POST {{host}}/api/watches?userId={{userId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productName": "Keyboard",
  "maxPrice": 0
}

###

### Create watch — invalid: missing userId query param → 400
POST {{host}}/api/watches
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productName": "Keyboard",
  "maxPrice": 99.99
}

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// GET /api/watches — List watches for a user
// Response 200: WatchResponse[]
// Response 400: string
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### List watches for user
GET {{host}}/api/watches?userId={{userId}}

###

### List watches — missing userId → 400
GET {{host}}/api/watches

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// GET /api/watches/{id} — Get a single watch
// Response 200: WatchResponse
// Response 400: string
// Response 404: (empty)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get watch by ID  (replace watchId with a real GUID after creating one)
GET {{host}}/api/watches/{{watchId}}?userId={{userId}}

###

### Get watch — not found (random GUID)
GET {{host}}/api/watches/ffffffff-ffff-ffff-ffff-ffffffffffff?userId={{userId}}

###

### Get watch — missing userId → 400
GET {{host}}/api/watches/{{watchId}}

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// PUT /api/watches/{id}/pause — Pause an active watch
// Response 200: WatchResponse (status = "paused")
// Response 400: string (missing userId OR invalid state transition)
// Response 404: (empty)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Pause watch
PUT {{host}}/api/watches/{{watchId}}/pause?userId={{userId}}

###

### Pause watch — invalid state transition (e.g. already paused) → 400
PUT {{host}}/api/watches/{{watchId}}/pause?userId={{userId}}

###

### Pause watch — not found → 404
PUT {{host}}/api/watches/ffffffff-ffff-ffff-ffff-ffffffffffff/pause?userId={{userId}}

###

### Pause watch — missing userId → 400
PUT {{host}}/api/watches/{{watchId}}/pause

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// PUT /api/watches/{id}/resume — Resume a paused watch
// Response 200: WatchResponse (status = "active")
// Response 400: string (missing userId OR invalid state transition)
// Response 404: (empty)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Resume watch
PUT {{host}}/api/watches/{{watchId}}/resume?userId={{userId}}

###

### Resume watch — invalid state transition (e.g. already active) → 400
PUT {{host}}/api/watches/{{watchId}}/resume?userId={{userId}}

###

### Resume watch — not found → 404
PUT {{host}}/api/watches/ffffffff-ffff-ffff-ffff-ffffffffffff/resume?userId={{userId}}

###

### Resume watch — missing userId → 400
PUT {{host}}/api/watches/{{watchId}}/resume

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// DELETE /api/watches/{id} — Cancel (soft-delete) a watch
// Response 204: (empty)
// Response 400: string (missing userId OR invalid state transition)
// Response 404: (empty)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Cancel watch
DELETE {{host}}/api/watches/{{watchId}}?userId={{userId}}

###

### Cancel watch — not found → 404
DELETE {{host}}/api/watches/ffffffff-ffff-ffff-ffff-ffffffffffff?userId={{userId}}

###

### Cancel watch — missing userId → 400
DELETE {{host}}/api/watches/{{watchId}}
